
bootia32.efi in /boot/efi/
bios choose boot from efi file, then choose this bootia32.efi
grub2 is inside this bootia32.efi

make sure it's fat32 file system

or mkdir -p /mnt/boot/efi
grub-install --efi-directory /mnt/boot/efi --boot-directory /boot --target i386-efi
then you can copy all the mod from /mnt/boot/grub/i386-efi/


android and windows,
mount -o x.iso /mnt
copy those /mnt/ files to usb-stick, make usb-stick with mkfs.vfat

linux distros, use dd if=x.iso of=/dev/sdb bs=512k
